<TITLE> Govt to approve new police legislation by year-end </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 20 (bdnews24.com)The interim cabinet will approve new legislation for modernisation of the police force by the end of the year, home adviser MA Matin said Sunday. At an inaugural session of the 'Second Police Executives Development Course' at Mirpur Police Staff College, the home adviser called on the police force Sunday to be more efficient, meritorious and public-oriented. He urged those present to build up the character of the police service morally, mentally and physically to protect people's lives and property and maintain law and order The government would take every step to assist in building up an efficient force, he added. Matin said the trend of crime has to be curbed; police officers must be respectful of the existing laws of the land so that they may in turn bring criminals under the law. He spoke of the caretaker government's intention of formulating police reform legislation, saying a modern police force cannot be run under the Police Act of 1861. New legislation for modernisation of the police force would be approved by the council of advisers by this year, he said. The government would assist by giving more resources, including funds and training facilities for police staff. Acting inspector general of police Nabo Bikram Kishore Tripura, Dhaka police commissioner Naim Ahmed, director of the staff college AKM Mahfuzul Haque and Mirpur deputy police commissioner Anwar Hossain were among those present at the inaugural session. bdnews
